[[Category:Geometry]]

{{Commons cat|Trigonometry}}
'''Trigonometry''' (from the [[Greek language|Greek]] ''trigonon'' = three angles and ''metro'' = measure) is a branch of [[mathematics]] dealing with [[angle]]s, [[triangle (geometry)|triangle]]s and '''[[trigonometric function]]s''' such as '''[[sine]]''', '''[[cosine]]''' and '''[[tangent]]'''. It has some relationship to [[geometry]], though there is disagreement on exactly what that relationship is; for some, trigonometry is just a subtopic of geometry.

