In [[robotics]], the '''manipulability ellipsoid''' is the geometric interpretation of the scaled [[eigenvector]]s resulting from the [[singular value decomposition]] of the [[Jacobian matrix and determinant|jacobian]] that describes a robot's motion.
[[Category:Robot control]] [[Category:Geometry]]
{{robotics-stub}}

{{unreferenced|date=August 2012}}
In [[mathematics]], the '''flatness''' (symbol: '''⏥''') of a [[surface (mathematics)|surface]] is the degree to which it approximates a [[Plane (mathematics)|mathematical plane]]. The term is often generalized for higher-dimensional [[manifold]]s to describe the degree to which they approximate the [[Euclidean space]] of the same dimensionality. (See ''[[curvature]]''.)

'''Flatness''' in [[homological algebra]] and [[algebraic geometry]] means, of an object <math>A</math> in an [[abelian category]], that <math>- \otimes A</math> is an [[exact functor]].  See [[flat module]] or, for more generality, [[flat morphism]].

