In mathematics, the '''Atiyah conjecture on configurations''' is a [[conjecture]] introduced by {{harvs|txt|last=Atiyah|authorlink=Michael Atiyah|year1=2000|year2=2001}} stating that a certain ''n'' by ''n'' [[matrix (mathematics)|matrix]] depending on ''n'' points in '''R'''<sup>3</sup> is always  [[non-singular matrix|non-singular]].

